Customizations such as Stylesheets (CSS), Custom HTML, and Layouts tend to break post-upgrade, especially to Confluence 5.x (see [Upgrade Notes|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/DOC/Confluence+5.0+Upgrade+Notes#Confluence5.0UpgradeNotes-Customthemes,layoutsandCSSwillprobablybreak]. We need a better way to prevent such upgrade pains on our customers' end, as many of our customers have extensive customizations that they wish to keep post-upgrade. Fixing them manually will only lengthen the upgrade task. (updating variables in layouts, changing CSS classes, etc). *Document changes* to stylesheets, layouts, JS, and limit their changes between releases, so that it will be less of a struggle.

